et (With Results) |publisher=[[Singapore Youth Olympic Games Organising Committee]] |accessdate=10 May 2018 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120525044748/http://www.singapore2010.sg/public/docroot/results/INF__WRW270000C75______________________00017000_PENG20100816190740000.pdf |archivedate=25 May 2012 }}</ref> She represented her country at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]]. She won silver medal at the [[2017 European Wrestling Championships]].<ref>{{cite news|title=A m\u00e1sodik magyar \u00e9rem is megvan a birk\u00f3z\u00f3 Eb-n|url=http://www.origo.hu/sport/egyeni/20170504-birkozo-europa-bajnoksag-ujvedik-nemeth-zsanett-ezustermes.html|publisher=www.origo.hu|language=Hungarian|date=4 May 2017|accessdate=11 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|- style=\"background:#CCCCCC\"\n!Year\n!Tournament\n!Venue\n!Result\n!Event\n|-\n|2010\n|[[Wrestling at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics|Youth Olympic Games]]\n|{{flagicon|SGP}} [[Singapore]], [[Singapore]]\n| align=\"center\" |7th\n|[[Wrestling at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics \u2013 Girls' freestyle 70 kg|Freestyle 70 kg]]\n|-\n|2013\n|[[2013 World Wrestling Championships|World Championships]]\n|{{flagicon|HUN}} [[Budapest]], [[Hungary]]\n| align=\"center\" |16th\n|[[2013 World Wrestling Championships \u2013 Women's freestyle 72 kg|Freestyle 72 kg]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2014\n|[[2014 European Wrestling Championships|European Championships]]\n|{{flagicon|FIN}} [[Vantaa]], [[Finland]]\n| align=\"center\" |5th\n|[[2014 European Wrestling Championships \u2013 Women's Freestyle 75 kg|Freestyle 75 kg]]\n|-\n|[[2014 World Wrestling Championships|World Championships]]\n|{{flagicon|UZB}} [[Tashkent]], [[Uzbekistan]]\n| align=\"center\" |15th\n|[[2014 World Wrestling Championships \u2013 Women's freestyle 75 kg|Freestyle 75 kg]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2015\n|[[Wrestling at the 2015 European Games|European Games]]\n|{{flagicon|AZ